'''152 mm gun M1935 (Br-2)''' ('''{{lang-ru|152-<U+043C><U+043C> <U+043F><U+0443><U+0448><U+043A><U+0430> <U+043E><U+0431><U+0440>. 1935 <U+0433>. (<U+0411><U+0440>-2)}}''') was a 152.4 mm [[Soviet]] heavy gun.

==Development==
Work on a long range 152 mm gun for Reserve of the Main Command units started in 1929, when the ''Bolshevik Plant'' in [[Saint Petersburg]] recieved from the Artillery Directorate requirements specifications for such a piece. The project recieved a factory index '''B-10'''. The first [[Gun barrel|barrel]] was ready in April 1932. Testing of the B-10 continued until 1935 and revealed a number of problems, including slow elevation, low rate of fire and short service life. As a result, the gun was not adopted. The two produced pieces were used for a series of experiments: their barrels were modified for firing pre-rifled projectiles and poligonal projectiles respectively; an attempt was made to improve elevation speed by use of an [[electric motor]]. The experiments did't produce practical results.

